What a magical night. By far the greatest achievement I've earned in my life.

Being chosen as one of 20 from hundreds (or even thousands) of LSPR students was one of the highlights of my college years.

Dengan bertujuan sekedar cari pengalaman dan kesibukan di kampus (karena dulu mahasiswa kupu2), sampai bisa masuk 10 besar dan terpilih sebagai Mr Best in Traditional Costume & 2nd Runner-Up Mr LSPR 2015.

I am thrilled and proud to have had the honour and opportunity of standing on that stage last night with my family, together with one mission: perform our best.

Tapi sekarang kita semua punya misi baru: membuat junior Mr & Ms LSPR 2016 nanti jauh lebih baik lagi dari kita! Selamat bertugas 2015!

Sometimes love comes and goes but my love towards football is eternal.

I've fallen passionately in love with the beautiful game itself since I was little. I love playing it, I love watching it. Safe to say, I'm a football enthusiast.

#MrMsLSPR2015

Performing Arts Communications, that is something you probably would never know at your ordinary universities. But here at The London School of Public Relations, students get to study about making a theatre production. Students get to develop some hidden talents they may have, which could be acting, singing, dancing, directing, pretty much whatever talent you can think of for a theatre production. I am proud to say that this pathway is not something that you get in other universities. This picture was taken when my ex-class was rehearsing for our theatre production, titled 'Rumors' at Campus A's parking lot. It was very tiring, me and friends were constantly getting exhausted at the end of the day after theatre rehearsals. But it is safe to say that all those struggles and hard work paid off. It was a great experience being able to perform in front of a big number of people. I am also proud to say that Rumors won 2 awards, including 5 more nominations. Certainly the best studying experience I've had so far, and there's only more good things to come. #LSPRMediaConvergence
